"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here with Sky's Fermented Foods. I want to talk a little bit about cover crops today again. And these are my cover crops. These are there just for the soil. I'm not producing anything out of them. Those are peas. That's rye grass, and underneath all that is some crimson clover. The peas and the clover are legumes, which means that they are high in nitrogen, and the grass, of course, is high in carbon. And that's important when you're putting down cover crops because what you want to eventually do when you cut these down is to have the legumes and the grasses and forbs, which I'll add next year, uh balance each other and get to a 30 to 1 ratio of carbon and nitrogen on the surface. And it should look a little something like this when you break it down. This was just three days ago, and look how it's already breaking down so nicely. This is because it's uh getting to the 30 to 1 ratio that compost happens at. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here with Sky's Fermented Foods.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 2.88,\n      \"duration\": 2.56,\n      \"confidence\": 0.981,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.996\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"du